{
  "text": "In children and adolescents, sedentary behavior (screen time) was associated with depression; however, evidence was based on cross-sectional studies. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] In adults, some reviews reported an association between sedentary behavior (television and other sedentary behaviors) and depressive symptoms [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] and postnatal depressive symptoms, [CITATION_6] also based on cross-sectional studies.",
